# Component & Code Patterns

Check this file before writing any UI code. These patterns apply to **every feature** — chat, feed, vault, onboarding, admin, auth, and anything new.

---

## Loading States

### Button loading → `<Spinner>`

Any button that triggers an async operation:

```tsx
import { Spinner } from "@/app/_components/spinner";

<Button disabled={loading}>
  {loading ? <Spinner /> : <>{t("save")} <Arrow s={14} /></>}
</Button>
```

❌ Never inline `<motion.span animate={{ rotate: 360 }}>` + `<BrandStar>` in a button again.

### Content loading → skeleton pulse

When a section is waiting for data to load:

```tsx
// Skeleton cards
<div className="grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-3">
  {[1, 2, 3].map((i) => (
    <div key={i} className="h-24 animate-pulse rounded-card bg-muted" />
  ))}
</div>
```

### Page-level loading text

When a full panel or page is loading:

```tsx
<p className="font-mono text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-muted-foreground">
  {t("section_title")}
</p>
<p className="font-sans text-xs text-muted-foreground mt-2">{t("loading")}</p>
```

