## Page Layouts

### App pages (with sidebar)

The app shell (sidebar + main wrapper) lives in the **(app) layout** (`AppShell` in `layout.tsx`). Route-level pages only render the content that goes inside `<main>` — no wrapper div, no `<AppSidebar>`, no auth/logout logic.

```tsx
// Page content only — shell is in layout
<div className="max-w-xl mx-auto px-6 py-8">
  {/* page content */}
</div>
```

Use `max-w-xl` for single-column content, `max-w-3xl` for wider layouts. For pages that need to control sidebar state (e.g. chat: mobile menu, person/group handlers), use **`useSidebarOverrides`** from `@/app/_libs/sidebar-overrides-context` to inject overrides; they are cleared on unmount.

### Auth pages (full-screen centered)

```tsx
import { AuthPageShell } from "@/app/(public)/auth/_components/auth-page-shell";

<AuthPageShell>
  <BrandLogo ... />
  <PageHeader title={t("title")} subtitle={t("subtitle")} />
  {/* form content */}
</AuthPageShell>
```

