## Async Data Fetching

Use a `cancelled` flag inside `useEffect` to prevent state updates after unmount:

```tsx
useEffect(() => {
  let cancelled = false;
  setLoading(true);

  async function load() {
    try {
      const { data, error } = await supabase.from("table").select("...");
      if (cancelled) return;
      if (error) { setError(error.message); return; }
      setData(data);
    } catch {
      if (!cancelled) setError(t("error_generic"));
    } finally {
      if (!cancelled) setLoading(false);
    }
  }

  load();
  return () => { cancelled = true; };
}, [dependency]);
```

